- Understand where system databases end and business databases start

Today understand environment-> no need theory

When you open MySQL Workbench focus ONLY on these:
1. Home Screen
- MySQL Connections
- Server status
- User sessions
This is where real work starts

2. SQL Editor (SPARK Imp. Area) -> This is your battlefield hahaa
You’ll use it to:
- Write SQL
- Execute queries
- Debug errors
- Test logic
We like engineers spend 90% of their our here

3. Navigator Panel (Left Side)
Shows:
- System databases
- Your business databases
- Tables, views, procedures
This tells you what data exists -> not how to query it

3/ Connecting to MySQL Server (Reality Step)
Typical Setup:
- Host: localhost
- Port: 3306
- Username: root
- Password: (set during installation)
If you can’t connect -> you can’t work -> you can’t be hired (Don't worry you're SPARK)

NEVER use system databases for practice
System DBs:
- mysql
- information_schema
- performance_schema
- sys

ALWAYS create your own business database, this is how professionalga companylo work chestham

CARETE DB: CREATE DATABASE company_db;
THEN: USE company_db;
EXAMPLE: CREATE TABLE employees (
    employee_id INT PRIMARY KeY,
    name VARCHAR(100),
    email VARCHAR(100),
    department VARCHAR(50),
    salary DECIMAL(10,2),
    joining_date DATE
);

Explain Like an SQL Developer from SPARK:
employee_id -> identity
VARCHAR -> flexible real-world text
DECIMAL -> money precision
DATE -> business timelines
This is not just syntax — this is business modeling in IT aas SQL Developer

SHOW TABLES;
DESCRIBE employees;
If this works -> your setup is perfectly working amigos

